lette (Rihanna song)|Russian Roulette]]\" <br/> \"[[Hard (Rihanna song)|Hard]]\" featuring [[Jeezy]] (tenth, March 6, 2010)\n| Four years, five months\n|<ref name=\"Gaga overtakes Rihanna in shortest time span to 10 number ones\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]]\n| \"[[Holiday (Madonna song)|Holiday/Lucky Star]]\" (first, September 24,1983) <br/> \"[[Like a Virgin (song)|Like a Virgin]]\" <br/> \"[[Material Girl]]\" <br/> \"[[Angel (Madonna song)|Angel]]/[[Into the Groove]]\" <!-- \"ANGEL\" and \"INTO THE GROOVE\" are DOUBLE-SIDED DANCE SINGLE, (like \"Holiday\"/\"Lucky Star\" reached number one\u2014as her first.). Therefore, Madonna's second double-sided dance single marks her FOURTH NUMBER-ONE DANCE SINGLR, not fifth, not sixth. Check more info on Billboard.com --> <br/> \"[[Open Your Heart (Madonna song)|Open Your Heart]]\" <br/> \"[[Causing a Commotion]]\" <br/> \"[[You Can Dance]]\" <br/> \"[[Like a Prayer (album)|Like a Prayer]]\" <br/> \"[[Express Yourself (Madonna song)|Express Yourself]]\" <br/> \"[[Keep It Together (song)|Keep It Together]]\" (tenth, March 31,1990)\n| Six years, six months\n| <ref name=\"Crave:Ninth\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8543166/madonna-crave-49th-number-1-dance-club-songs-chart|title=Madonna Adds 49th No. 1 on Dance Club Songs Chart With Swae Lee Collab 'Crave'|work=Billboard|accessdate=November 8, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n{{Clear}}\n\n==Song achievements==\n\n===Shortest climbs to number-one===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Number of <br /> weeks\n!Artist(s)\n!Song\n!Year(s)\n|-\n|rowspan=2|<center>3</center>\n|[[ABC (band)|ABC]]\n|\"[[Be Near Me]]\"<ref name=\"BeNearMe\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vCQEAAAAMBAJ&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=true|title=Billboard magazine, issue dated 28 September 1985|via=Google Books|accessdate=September 15, 2015|page=44}}</ref>\n|1985\n|-\n|[[Colonel Abrams]] \n|\"[[I'm Not Gonna 